The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has formally cleared all the six aspirants jostling for the party’s ticket ahead of Osun governorship race scheduled for July 16. The Chairman of the screening committee and former Attorney General and Minister of Justice, Muhammed Adoke disclosed this on Thursday, while submitting the Committee’s report to PDP National Organising Secretary, Umaru Nature. The aspirants cleared by the committee, According to Adoke, are; Senator Ademola Adeleke, Dr Akin Ogunbiyi, Hon Omirin Emmanuel Olusanya, Dele Adeleke, former Secretary to Osun State government, Alhaji Abdulateef Akinbade and Mr Dotun Babayemi. Ladoja, Akala, Deputy Governor, Others Pay Last Respect To Late… Sanwo-Olu, Others Advocate Tourism-Boosted IGR Adoke, who said that none of the candidates was disqualified, told the National Working Committee (NWC) that the exercise was thoroughly conducted in line with party guidelines and constitution. Commending the committee members for their selfless service, the PDP National Organising Secretary, Hon. Umar Bature, in his remarks, assured that the leadership of the party will give aspirants for every elective position equal opportunity. Bature said: “On behalf of the National Working Committee (NWC) of our party, I sincerely thank this committee for a job well done. “Osun is one of the most important states to our party and we believe with the job this committee has done, all the aspirants will be glad of the outcome. The aspirants will see that we have done the best in their interest.”